
Die Oracle Certified Associate (OCA) Java Programmer Prüfung umfasst eine Vielzahl von Methoden und Konzepten,
die Sie kennen und anwenden müssen. Hier ist eine Übersicht der wichtigsten Methoden und Konzepte,
die für die OCA-Prüfung relevant sind:
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Methoden aus der Object Klasse
equals(Object obj)
hashCode()
toString()
getClass()
clone()
finalize()
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
String Klasse Methoden
charAt(int index)
concat(String str)
contains(CharSequence s)
equals(Object obj)
equalsIgnoreCase(String anotherString)
length()
substring(int beginIndex)
substring(int beginIndex, int endIndex)
toLowerCase()
toUpperCase()
trim()
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
StringBuilder Klasse Methoden
append(String str)
insert(int offset, String str)
delete(int start, int end)
deleteCharAt(int index)
reverse()
toString()
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Wrapper Klassen Methoden (z.B. Integer, Double, etc.)
parseXxx(String s) (z.B. parseInt(String s))
valueOf(String s)
valueOf(primitive value)
xxxValue() (z.B. intValue(), doubleValue())
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Collections Framework Methoden
List Interface (z.B. ArrayList, LinkedList)-----------------------------------------------------------------------------
add(E e)
add(int index, E element)
remove(int index)
remove(Object o)
get(int index)
set(int index, E element)
size()
clear()
contains(Object o)
Set Interface (z.B. HashSet, TreeSet)-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
add(E e)
remove(Object o)
contains(Object o)
size()
clear()
Map Interface (z.B. HashMap, TreeMap)-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------
put(K key, V value)
get(Object key)
remove(Object key)
containsKey(Object key)
containsValue(Object value)
keySet()
values()
entrySet()
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Arrays Methoden
sort()
binarySearch()
equals()
copyOf()
fill()
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Java.util.Arrays Methoden
asList(T... a)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Math Klasse Methoden
abs()
max()
min()
pow()
sqrt()
random()
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Exception Handling
try-catch-finally Blocks
throw Statement
throws Clause
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Java Language Features
Primitive Data Types and their Wrapper Classes
Autoboxing and Unboxing
Enhanced for Loop (for-each loop)
Varargs
Static Imports
Access Modifiers (public, protected, private, default)
Inheritance and Polymorphism
Abstract Classes and Interfaces
Static and Instance Initializers
Constructors, including Overloading
Method Overloading and Overriding
Encapsulation and Use of this Keyword
Casting between Primitive Types and Reference Types
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Java 8 Features (if applicable)
Lambda Expressions
Functional Interfaces (e.g., Predicate, Function, Consumer)
Method References
Stream API Basics
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Date and Time API (if applicable)
LocalDate
LocalTime
LocalDateTime
Period
Duration
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Diese Liste umfasst die wesentlichen Methoden und Konzepte,
die Sie für die OCA Java Programmer Prüfung beherrschen sollten.